oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Artist In Residence - Vince Gill - 2009-02-24
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Performance by Vince Gill from the Ford Theater at the Country Music Hall of Fame and Museum on February 24, 2009.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Vince Gill
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: Vince gill on vocal/guitar with Pete Wiseman on piano. Performances include "When I Call Your Name" -- "Pretty Little Adriana" -- "Look At Us" -- "What The Cowgirls Do" -- "Oklahoma Dust" -- "The Rock Of Your Love" -- "When I'm Good And Gone" Leslie Satcher -- "Gypsy Boots" Leslie Satcher -- "Bread And Water" -- "Faint Of Heart" -- "Which Way Will You Go" -- "If You Ever Have Forever In Your Mind" -- "Pocketful of Gold" -- "The Key To Life" -- "One More Last Chance" with Jerry Douglas -- "Go Rest High On That Mountain" with Jerry Douglas -- "Liza Jane" with Jerry Douglas -- "Take This Country Back" -- "La Bamba" Billy Garcia -- "Little Brother" -- "Threaten Me With Heaven".
